Clint Gee planned to reunite his mother, Elizabeth Hobbs, with his father, Alex Gee, who died in 1964 .
Mr Gee made the almost six hour journey from his Brisbane home to Wandoan in regional Queensland .
But a council 'co-ordination error' meant work had not been done to bury the pair .
He said the council process was 'a bloody bit stupid, but I had to do it'